.content__section--intro.home__section.home-intro.page-home
  .container-fluid
    .jumbotron.jumbotron-flush.home-intro__jumbotron
      .home-intro__slider-container
        .row
          .col-10.offset-1.col-sm-6.offset-sm-3.col-md-5.offset-md-6
            .home-intro__slider-wrapper
              .home-intro__slider
                = image_tag 'home-slider-00.jpg', class: 'home-intro__slider-image active'
                = image_tag 'home-slider-01.jpg', class: 'home-intro__slider-image'
                = image_tag 'home-slider-02.jpg', class: 'home-intro__slider-image'
                = image_tag 'home-slider-03.jpg', class: 'home-intro__slider-image'
      .home-intro__hl-container
        .row
          .col-12.col-sm-9.col-md-8
            %h1.display-1.home-intro__hl Standard for secure resource exchange and interoperability
    .row.home-intro__button-row
      .col-12.col-md-6.col-lg-12
        %a.btn.btn-cta.home-intro__button{:href => "/users/sign_up"} Get started
        %a.btn.home-intro__button{:href => "/pages/about"} Learn more
    .row
      .col.col-md-8.col-lg-6
        %p.lead
          RISE Project—Research Infrastructure for the Study of Eurasia—is a digital research infrastructure developed by the Max Planck Institute for the History of Science. It is a pioneering approach for resource dissemination and emerging data analytics in the humanities. Its various technical components facilitate the secure linkage between third-party research tools and various third-party textual collections (both licensed and open-access ones) via a standard API called <a href='/pages/doc_for_developers'>SHINE</a>.
.home-get-started.home__section
  .container-fluid
    .row
      .col-12.col-md-4.home-get-started__col
        %h3
          %small Get started
          For Resource Providers
        %p
          Reach more users, connect easily to research tools and facilitate resource exchange securely!
          Implement SHINE-compatible API endpoints to manage access to your resources and to make them available via the RISE Catalog.
          Use the RISE-RP Toolkit to host and publish the resources that you want to share via SHINE.
        %ul.list-unstyled
          %li
            %a.link-with-arrow{:href => "/pages/doc_for_developers"} See the SHINE documentation
          %li
            %a.link-with-arrow{:href => "https://github.com/RISE-MPIWG", target: '_blank'} Grab the RP Toolkit
      .col-12.col-md-4.home-get-started__col
        %h3
          %small Get started
          For Research Tool Developers
        %p
          Connect easily to resource repositories and make data import painless for your users!
          Implement SHINE-compatible API endpoints to securely consume resources available via the RISE Catalog.
          Use the RISE-JS Toolkit to allow users to browse and import SHINE-compatible resources directly in your tool's user interface.
        %ul.list-unstyled
          %li
            %a.link-with-arrow{:href => "/pages/doc_for_developers"} See the SHINE documentation
          %li
            %a.link-with-arrow{:href => "https://github.com/RISE-MPIWG", target: '_blank'} Grab the JS Toolkit
          %li
            %a.link-with-arrow{:href => "/resources"} Browse the RISE Catalog
      .col-12.col-md-4.home-get-started__col
        %h3
          %small Get started
          For Research Institutes
        %p
          Gain unprecedented access to textual resources in a machine-readable format, so that they can be analyzed in research tools in a seamless and legal research workflow! Please sign up and visit the RISE Catalog to view the resources you have access to based on your affiliation.
        %ul.list-unstyled
          %li
            %a.link-with-arrow{:href => "/resources"} Browse the RISE Catalog
