.home-use-cases.home__section
  .container-fluid
    %h2.display-1 Use cases
    .jumbotron.home-use-cases__jumbotron
      .row.home-use-cases__row
        .col-8.offset-2.col-sm-4.offset-sm-4.offset-md-1.align-self-center.home-use-cases__img-col
          .home-use-cases__img-container
            = image_tag 'case-logart.jpg', class: 'home-use-cases__image active'
            = image_tag 'case-markus.png', class: 'home-use-cases__image'
            = image_tag 'case-kanseki.jpg', class: 'home-use-cases__image'
            = image_tag 'case-arabic-poetry.png', class: 'home-use-cases__image'
          .home-use-cases__arrow-left
            %span.icon.icon-arrow-left
          .home-use-cases__arrow-right
            %span.icon.icon-arrow-right
        .col-md-6.align-self-center
          %ul.list-unstyled.home-use-cases__text-list
            %li.home-use-cases__text.active
              %h3 LoGaRT: Local Gazetteers Research Tools
              %p LoGaRT is a suite of digital tools developed by the Max Planck Institute for the History of Science. Its purposes are to transform texts in Chinese local gazetteers into structured data, to perform systematic analyses, and to visualize research results. LoGaRT uses the SHINE API to ingest local gazetteer texts across multiple resource providers and the RISE middleware to manage user access to those texts from licensed databases.
            %li.home-use-cases__text
              %h3 MARKUS
              %p MARKUS is a tool that can automatically tag personal names, place names, temporal references, and bureaucratic offices in Chinese and Korean texts. After implementing the JS Toolkit, MARKUS users can now browse the RISE Catalog and select resources for analysis directly in MARKUS’s interface, without having to manually prepare the texts and upload them one by one. The RISE middleware also allows analysis on licensed texts, which was previously impossible, in MARKUS.
            %li.home-use-cases__text
              %h3 Kanseki Repository
              %p Kanseki Repository, colloquially known as Kanripo, is a collection of open-access pre-modern Chinese texts stored in GitHub repositories. The RISE middleware mapped SHINE API endpoints with Kanripo’s GitHub repositories, allowing users programmatic access to the texts via SHINE API or in the RISE Catalog in a standardized fashion.
            %li.home-use-cases__text
              %h3 Personal collection of Arabic poetry
              %p Mahmood Kozae, a scholar from Freie Universität Berlin, has a rich collection of Arabic poetry. Using the RP Toolkit, he was able to quickly and easily host it online via the RISE Catalog and make it retrievable to the public via the SHINE API. The RISE middleware also allows him to manage access rights to his collection on a granular level.
.home-join-community.home__section
  .container-fluid
    %h2.display-1 Join the community
    .row
      .col-12.col-md-6.home-join-community__form-col
        %h3 Get in touch!
        %p Get in touch with your specific collections, tools, or research needs and see how you can benefit from RISE and SHINE! Tell us what you need, and our team will arrange for individual meetings with you for further discussions.
        = form_for Contact.new do |f|
          .form-group
            %label.visually-hidden{:for => "{{TODO scope}}-name"} Name
            = f.text_field :name, placeholder: 'Name', type: :text, class: 'form-control'
          .form-group
            %label.visually-hidden{:for => "{{TODO scope}}-email"} Email address
            = f.text_field :email, placeholder: 'Email', type: :email, class: 'form-control'
          .form-group
            %label.visually-hidden{:for => "{{TODO scope}}-message"} Message
            = f.text_area :message, placeholder: 'Message', rows: '6', class: 'form-control'
          %button.btn.home-join-community__submit-btn{:type => "submit"} Submit
      .col-12.col-md-6
        %h3 Have questions?
        %p See who’s already using RISE and SHINE by visiting the ‘Community’ page. Or, check out the discussion forum, where community members interact with one another. You can see how people have used RISE and SHINE and what questions they have had. Join in on the fun by posting your queries there!
        %div
          %a.btn.btn-cta.btn-sm{:href => "/pages/community"} Go to ‘Community’ page
          %br/
          %br/
          %a.btn.btn-cta.btn-sm{:href => "https://groups.google.com/d/forum/rise--shine", :target => "_blank"} Exchange ideas
